        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2431476794" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13368364556445608631">I liked this; didn’t love it; too many ‘no freaking way would this happen in reality’ moments. Even though there were nigglings in my head that wiggled in, it was still a gripping page turner.<br/><br/>3 girls vanished from a summer camp more than 15 years ago. Emma, who had shared a cabin with them, is now being called back to the camp as they reinvigorate it to reopen it.<br/>But Emma recalls more than she wants and beneath her own fears, she recognizes her own lies and her role in their disappearance.<br/><br/>Some g</span>
  <span id="freeText13368364556445608631" style="display:none">I liked this; didn’t love it; too many ‘no freaking way would this happen in reality’ moments. Even though there were nigglings in my head that wiggled in, it was still a gripping page turner.<br /><br />3 girls vanished from a summer camp more than 15 years ago. Emma, who had shared a cabin with them, is now being called back to the camp as they reinvigorate it to reopen it.<br />But Emma recalls more than she wants and beneath her own fears, she recognizes her own lies and her role in their disappearance.<br /><br />Some good twists and an unexpected ending. Will check another Sager out. 3.5 ⭐️ rounded down to 3⭐️ as it failed to meet my reality meter.<br /><br /><br /></span>
